title: Kirksville boys take fourth at NCMC cross country meet
text: Kirksville boys take fourth at NCMC cross country meet Comment Kirksville Daily Express - Kirksville, MO Writer Posted Oct. 15, 2015 at 8:34 PM Posted Oct. 15, 2015 at 8:34 PM HIGHSCHOOLCROSS COUNTRY Kirksville at NCMCMeet Girls - Lauren Gaines, 2nd place finish, 22:20; Yordie Schneider, 9th place finish, 23:51; Skylar Kertz, 15th place finish, 24:53; Emily Eital, 21st place finish, 25:55 Boys - 4th place team finish; Duncan Clark, 2nd place finish, 17:20; Nolon Carter, 21st place finish, 20:11; Garret Johnson, 26th place finish, 20:55; Parker Petersen, 28th place finish, 21:02; Sam Tiedemann, 32nd place finish, 21:53; Curtis Burgeon, 34th place finish, 21:54; Ryan Everette, 26th place finish, 26:14 “It's an extremely tough course and I thought both the boys and girls team stepped up well tonight,”Kirksville coach Geoff Hutton said. Kirksville Daily Express - Kirksville, MO Writer
